0901 - Super Investors flow rows (Sammaan Capital, TV Today Network,
Nazara, etc) were coming from /api/v1/super-investor-flow with the
company name string in the ticker field. The home rail rendered them
without a ticker chip, visually misaligning them from the roster rows
that DO have tickers. Plus all 3 collided into a single /super-
investors fallback URL because none had a real NSE symbol.

Fix:
  - New resolveCompanyToTicker() reverse-maps company names to tickers
    using NSE_TICKER_NAMES + a FLOW_EXTRAS table covering marquee-
    investor flow names (SAMMAANCAP, TVTODAY, NAZARA, JBCHEPHARM,
    POLYMED, RELAXO, PIDILITIND, ASIANPAINT, BAJFINANCE, TITAN).
  - Home consumer always reserves the ticker column width (70px).
    When ticker is resolved, shows it. When not, shows an em-dash so
    the visual alignment is preserved across all rows.
  - Resolved tickers link to /stock-sheet?ticker=X; unresolved still
    route to /super-investors.

0902 - Special Situations row reformatted for institutional density:

Visual changes:
  - Padding 4px/6px -> 7px/10px (more breathing room)
  - Gap 6 -> 8
  - Ticker chip font 11 -> 12, width 84 -> 78 (still aligns)
  - Headline font 11 -> 12
  - Event-type pill: full label not raw enum:
      MA           -> "M&A"
      BUYBACK_TENDER -> "Buyback (tender)"
      PREFERENTIAL -> "Pref. allotment"
      RIGHTS_ISSUE -> "Rights issue"
      Open offer / Demerger / Spin-off / Stake sale / Acquisition all
      rendered as readable text not screaming caps.
  - DIRECT / NEWS chips renamed FILED / REPORTED (clearer for an
    institutional reader: filed = structured disclosure, reported =
    news scrape).
  - New market chip (Indian flag for IN, US flag for US tickers),
    heuristic by ticker length + override set for short-form Indian
    tickers (TCS, LIC, IOC, ITC, BPCL, NTPC, ONGC, IRFC, CMS, IDFC,
    IGL, MGL, CGCL, HUL, SBI, GAIL, IDBI, OIL, GIC, IOB).

Content changes:
  - Deal value extraction: parses Rs X Cr / $X bn / $X mn from the
    headline and renders as an orange monospace pill (visible deal
    size at a glance).
  - Tooltip now shows full deal context: ticker (market) · type ·
    subcategory · headline · announced / next-catalyst dates · deal
    value · expected alpha.

For Bliss-GVS-Anupam-Rasayan-style deals the row will now read:
  [FILED] [🇮🇳 IN] [BLISSGVS] [M&A] [Rs 1,369 Cr] Anupam Rasayan to
  acquire up to 43% stake in Bliss GVS Pharma  +alpha  today
